On Thursday 29 March Daily
Sun ran a story headlined “Killer sent to prison”. The report quoted Simon Louw,
a relative of one of the victims, as saying “We don’t need such people in our society. I’m happy they
have been permanently removed from society.”Mr
Louw has denied saying this.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>In
addition, the report stated that the killers broke into “their house”, whereas
the events actually took place at a friend’s home.Daily
Sun regrets the errors and takes this opportunity to retract the story and
apologise to Mr Louw for the errors.    We remain committed to delivering ethical and
truthful reporting and therefor also apologise to SunReaders with the
commitment to redouble our efforts to ensure you get the quality of news you deserve.